June 17, 2019 at 9:36 PM ·

School board elections for the Viborg-Hurley School District are Tuesday, June 18th. This is an At Large election so all patrons of the Viborg-Hurley School District can vote. Viborg can vote at City Hall and Hurley can vote at the Middle School in Hurley. Polls are open 7AM to 7 PM.

Remember every election is determined by those who show up!!

Viborg-Hurley Athletic Boosters
November 11, 2018 at 3:29 PM ·

A GREAT new way to support the Cougar Athletes! Continue your normal Amazon shopping while giving back to the Viborg-Hurley Athletic Boosters! No Fees! No Hassel! Click the link below to get started!

OR
For Mobile App Follow these easy steps!
1. If you have the Amazon App installed you should remove it.
2. Now load Safari (the iPhone internet browser) and go to smile.amazon.co.uk.
3. Tap the 'share' button on the bottom of the screen.
4. Tap the 'Add to Home Screen' icon.

Please share and help spread the word!

post_text:
Brandy Skonhovd:

We are in need of desserts for the visitation service Wednesday night. Please comment if you are able to supply bars. They would like A lot of Special K bars since that was Brady’s favorite, and we are working on getting twin bing bars since they were Kelley’s favorite. They can be dropped off at the community center on Wednesday from 9:00 to 4:00. If you need to drop them off before then, please contact Brandy Skonhovd at 605-359-7690 or Melissa Whiddon at 334-782-3441. Also please spread the word! Thank you to everyone for all your generosity!
